Criterion: Subjects who tested positive for RBD and neutralization antibodies at baseline

Subjects with no baseline sample available and whose RBD and neutralization antibody reached the peak after first-dose immunization (indicative of memory from previous infection) and were nucleocapsid (NC) antibody-positive.
Mongolian participants who had been fully vaccinated with one of four COVID vaccines: Pfizer/BioNTech, AstraZeneca, Sputnik V, and Sinopharm
Boosted Solid organ transplant recipients without known prior infection.
Adolescents with myocarditis after SARS-CoV-2 mRNA vaccination.
Participants with SARS-CoV-2 infection or have a history of infection.
